## Create an IM Group

Create a IM Group under your account

> Definition

```shell
POST https://api.zoom.us/v2/im/groups
```

> Example Request

```shell
$ curl https://api.zoom.us/v2/im/groups \
   -d '{
    "name": "string",
    "type": "string",
    "search_by_domain": "boolean",
    "search_by_account": "boolean",
    "search_by_ma_account": "boolean"
}'
```

> Example Response

```text
201 Created
```

```json
{
    "id": "string",
    "name": "string",
    "total_members": "integer",
    "search_by_domain": "boolean",
    "search_by_account": "boolean",
    "search_by_ma_account": "boolean"
}
```

Body Arguments | &nbsp;
--- | ---
name *optional*<div class="maxLength">128</div> | Group name, must be unique in one account
type *optional*<div class="default">normal</div> | IM Group type<div class="enum">`normal` Only members can see the group automatically. Other people can search members in the group.<br/>`shared` All people in the account can see the group and members automatically<br/>`restricted` Nobody can see the group or search members except the members in the group<br/></div>
search_by_domain *optional* | Members can search others in the same email domain
search_by_account *optional* | Members can search others under same account
search_by_ma_account *optional* | Members can search others under same master account, including all sub accounts

